      "comment_id" : 121816061,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "as just commented: This change breaks other functionality. So you must write  &lt;argLine&gt;@{argLine} -Dfile.encoding=UTF-8&lt;/argLine&gt;"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2928406,
      "reputation" : 2685,
      "user_id" : 2509287,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/80a128e8763bb13482d357f65ecdfb44?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "softandsafe",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2509287/softandsafe"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 159,
    "last_activity_date" : 1759749752,
    "last_edit_date" : 1759749752,
    "creation_date" : 1373961604,
    "answer_id" : 17671104,
    "question_id" : 17656475,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have found a &quot;solution&quot; myself:</p>\n<p>I had to pass the encoding into the maven-surefire-plugin, but the usual</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;encoding&gt;${project.build.sourceEncoding}&lt;/encoding&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>did not work. I still have no idea why, but when i pass the command line arguments into the plugin, the tests works as they should:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;properties&gt;\n    &lt;project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;UTF-8&lt;/project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;\n&lt;/properties&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;plugin&gt;\n      &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;\n      &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n      &lt;version&gt;2.15&lt;/version&gt;\n      &lt;configuration&gt;\n        &lt;argLine&gt;${argLine} -Dfile.encoding=${project.build.sourceEncoding}&lt;/argLine&gt;\n      &lt;/configuration&gt;\n&lt;/plugin&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>You need to include <code>${argLine}</code> - otherwise other plugins that also modify list of arguments, like JaCoCo, will stop working.</p>\n<p>Thanks for all your responses and additional comments!</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7567,
      "reputation" : 10522,
      "user_id" : 13189,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 75,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/tKLRf.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "eckes",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13189/eckes"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1410529797,
    "last_edit_date" : 1410529797,
    "creation_date" : 1391140674,
    "answer_id" : 21472163,
    "question_id" : 17656475,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Your problem is not the encoding of the source file (and therefore the String inside your class file) but the Problem is the encoding of <code>System.out</code>'s implicite <code>PrintStream</code>. It uses <code>file.encoding</code> which represents the System encoding, and this is in Windows the ANSI codepage.</p>\n\n<p>You would have to set up a <code>PrintWriter</code> with the OEM code page (or you use the class which is intended for this: <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/io/Console.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Console</a>).</p>\n\n<p>See also various bugs around this in: <a href=\"http://bugs.java.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=4153167\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://bugs.java.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=4153167</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1491940,
      "reputation" : 414,
      "user_id" : 1398839,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 33,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/M9CAW.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Eric Martinez",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1398839/eric-martinez"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1411068220,
    "creation_date" : 1411068220,
    "answer_id" : 25920781,
    "question_id" : 17656475,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>this works for me:</p>\n\n<pre><code>...\n &lt;properties&gt;\n        **&lt;project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;ISO-8859-1&lt;/project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;\n        &lt;project.reporting.outputEncoding&gt;ISO-8859-1&lt;/project.reporting.outputEncoding&gt;**\n    &lt;/properties&gt;\n...\n  &lt;build&gt;\n    &lt;finalName&gt;Project&lt;/finalName&gt;\n\n    &lt;sourceDirectory&gt;src&lt;/sourceDirectory&gt;\n    &lt;plugins&gt;\n      &lt;plugin&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;2.3.2&lt;/version&gt;\n        &lt;configuration&gt;\n          &lt;source&gt;1.6&lt;/source&gt;\n          &lt;target&gt;1.6&lt;/target&gt;\n          **&lt;encoding&gt;${project.build.sourceEncoding}&lt;/encoding&gt;**\n        &lt;/configuration&gt;\n      &lt;/plugin&gt;\n      &lt;plugin&gt;\n        &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-war-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n        &lt;version&gt;2.2&lt;/version&gt;\n        &lt;configuration&gt;\n          &lt;warSourceDirectory&gt;WebContent&lt;/warSourceDirectory&gt;\n        &lt;/configuration&gt;\n      &lt;/plugin&gt;\n    &lt;/plugins&gt;\n  &lt;/build&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2753950,
      "reputation" : 535,
      "user_id" : 2372612,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 20,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/pSruG.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "David Vonka",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2372612/david-vonka"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1500393793,
    "creation_date" : 1500393793,
    "answer_id" : 45171952,
    "question_id" : 17656475,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had a really resilient problem of this kind and setting environmental variable</p>\n\n<pre><code>MAVEN_OPTS=-Dfile.encoding=UTF-8\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>fixed the issue for me.</p>\n"
  }, {
